Metaventrite (
Fig. 12
) unmodified, with short metaventral intercoxal process (
Fig. 12
; 
mtvp
) broadly separating metacoxae, with distinctly concave posterior margin.

Legs (
Fig. 1
) long and slender, front legs with modifications: protrochanter (
Fig. 13
; 
tr1
) with long ventral thornlike projection, and profemur (
Fig. 14
) distinctly enlarged in relation to meso- and metafemur, with ventral margin bisinuate, anterior surface impressed near sub-basal third and near middle, with sub-basal impression covered with tiny tubercles and sub-median impression filled with short, dense setae.
